The paper deals with techniques for reducing the dimension of polynomials in Gaussian space while preserving their correlation structure, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The applications of the technique involve problems in computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), such as finding optimal partitions and simulating joint distributions. The paper also involves the use of probabilistic methods, which is a common theme in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
